result.execSummary:
The defendant Alejandro Alvarez Hernandez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Child Pornography, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.12(1m).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Alejandro  Alvarez Hernandez in court, in custody, with attorney Eduardo M. Borda.   Brian Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Patrick Ryan appeared as interpreter. Parties proceed to sentencing on Ct. 2. 

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 2:
- Total sentence: 8 years (Initial Confinement: 4 years - 159 days credit, Extended Supervision: 4 years) 
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration 
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Substance Abuse Program. 
- Court Costs totaling $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision; alternate 6 days jail - consecutive. 
- Restitution totaling $2500.00 for 5 images (5 x 500 p/image) to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision.
- DNA Surcharge totaling $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision; alternate 5 days jail - consecutive.
- Conditions of Extended Supervision: No unsupervised contact with anyone under 18 years of age. Not be in possession of the Internet without permission of his Agent. Forfeit items that were seized. Register as a sex offender.  DNA Sample if not yet provided.
Sentencing hearing on September 8, 2014 at 02:45 pm.
